              <msItem n="1" xml:id="a1" defective="unknown">
                <locus from="1b" to="10a">Foll. 1b-10a</locus>
                <author ref=""/>
                <title ref="" type="supplied">A chronological introduction</title>
              </msItem>
              <msItem n="2" xml:id="a2" defective="true">
                <locus from="10a" to="69">Foll. 10a-69</locus>
                <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/354">Athanasius of Alexandria</author>
                <title ref="" type="supplied">The Festal Letters of Athanasius</title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܐܓܪ̈ܬܐ ܥܐ̈ܕܢܝܬܐ ܕܩܕܝܫܐ ܡܪܝ ܐܬܢܣܝܘܣ
                  <locus from="10a" to="10a"/>
                </rubric>
                <note>These letters were printed by <persName>Dr. Cureton</persName> in the order of their discovery, <placeName>London</placeName>, <date when="1848" calendar="Gregorian">1848</date>; and re-edited, in correct sequence and with a Latin translation, by <persName>Cardinal Mai</persName> in his <bibl>Nova Patrum Bibliotheca, tom. vi.</bibl> (see also <bibl>Migne, Patrol. Cursus Complet., Ser. Greaca, t. ii. col. 1339, etc.</bibl>). They were translated into German by <persName>Dr. Larsow</persName>, <placeName>Leipzig</placeName>, <date when="1852" calendar="Gregorian">1852</date>; and into English by <persName>Dr. Burgess</persName>, in <bibl><persName>Dr. Pusey's</persName> Library of Fathers of the Holy Catholic Church, 1854</bibl>, where the two leaves (foll. <locus from="41">41</locus> and <locus from="48">48</locus>) are printed, which were added to the manuscript since the appearance of the Curetonian text. Of the letters only twenty remain, the last of which is imperfect.</note>
                <listBibl>
                  <bibl>Dr. Cureton, Letters, London, 1848.</bibl>
                  <bibl>Cardinal Mai, Letters with Latin translation, Nova Patrum Bibliotheca, tom. vi.</bibl>
                  <bibl>Migne, Patrol. Cursus Complet., Ser. Greaca, t. ii. col. 1339, etc.</bibl>
                  <bibl>Dr. Larsow, Letters (German trans.), Leipzig, 1852.</bibl>
                  <bibl>Dr. Burgess, Letters (English trans.), in Dr. Pusey's Library of the Fathers of the Holy Catholic Church, 1854.</bibl>
                </listBibl>
                </msItem>
