              <decoDesc/>
              <additions>
                <p/>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                    <locus from="1a" to="1a"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote2"></ref>
                    <p>On fol. 1 a there is written in large, open characters, a note stating that the book be¬longed to the convent of S. Mary Deipara:</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܠܕܝܪܐ ܩܕ܏ܝܫ ܕܝܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܐܣܩ̈ܝܛܝܣ ܟܠ ܕܩܪܐ ܢܨ̇ܠ̣ܐ ܥܠܝ ܡܛܠ ܡܪܢ.</quote></p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                    <locus from="1b" to="1b"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote3"></ref>
                    <p>From a note on the margin of fol. 1 b it appears that a history of the blessed Virgin and a life of Simeon Stylites (<ref target="http://syriaca.org/manuscript/169">Add. 14,484</ref>?) were at one time bound with these letters.</p> <!-- Is this the proper way to reference an outside xml document? -->
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܘܬܘܒ ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܝ̇ܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ. ܘܕܫܡܥܘܢ ܕܐܣܛܘܼܢܐ. </quote></p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                    <locus from="1b" to="1b"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote4"></ref>
                    <p>On the same page a poor monk named Jacob has recorded his inability to under¬stand the introduction in these words:</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">܀ ܐܓܪܬܐ ܕܐܬܢܣܝܘܣ܀ ܐܢܐ ܝܥܩܘܒ ܚ̇ܛܝܐ ܩ̇ܪܝܬ ܠܗܕܐ ܐܓܪܬܐ ܘܠܐ ܝ̇ܕܥ ܐܢܐ ܡܘܢ ܐ̇ܡܪܐ ܫܒܘܩ ܠܝ.</quote></p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
